content: Good Rook Substitute. Partner AI needs a bit of tweeking, strategy is odd and sometimes not good. For example, it plays the rook out of turn like a new player would and after several games it doesn't improve or learn. Opposing team plays well though. Outside this, the game allows customizing the rules so I can play tournament rules instead of Kentucky Discard (bidder leads). One thing I would ask for is for 2-4 player or possibly online play with game invite. Playing AI is ok but gets old.

content: A little buggy or I'd rate it a 5-star. After the 7-3-2020 update, the red 1 is not scoring leaving only 165 possible points. That really increases the possibility of getting set so I dropped my rating. Also, the game has always locked up if you let your phone go on standby after naming trump and discarding five but before playing the first card. The program comes back thinking you haven't discarded 5 cards and won't let you proceed. Fix the bugs and I'll re-rate you.
replyContent: I'm sorry about these troubles. These were an issues that should be fixed in the version just released today. Let me know if you continue to experience issues after updating.

Rook is a family tradition.  I've been waiting for Blackbird to be available for Android.  Gameplay is smooth and the interface is intuitive.    I wish the game's AI was a little sharper.  I'd prefer the option to play "low Rook" (where the Rook is valued as the lowest trump card, not the highest).  EDIT: my mistake, you *can* play "low Rook."  :)    And, if I could really dream, I'd like the option of bidding "uptown" (1, 14, 13, 12...) or "downtown" (1, 2, 3, 4...).   But, I acknowledge that most Rook players don't play that way.  NOTE:  I'd also appreciate an option where the winner of the last hand gets bonus points (rather than just the points in the kitty/nest).   E.g., I've often played where the winner of the last trick gets 20 points.
replyContent: Good feedback!  I'm working on improving the AI.  Also, you can create a rule set that will allow you to play with the Blackbird as the lowest card.  Go to Settings to create your own rule set and you can change a bunch of things.

content: Good game but has a few flaws.  There should be an undo button in case you play the wrong card in error.   I also don't think that we need to be told what cards to play.   I mean I get that we have to follow suit, but if we're void in a suit we should be able to sluff instead of being forced to play a trump.   All in all a good game.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback!  You can create a rule set that will allow you to sluff instead of being forced to play trump.  Go to Settings to create your own rule set and you can change a bunch of things.  FYI, you can also go to http://android-blackbird.uservoice.com to submit other ideas and vote on them!
